      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, reduce the heat to medium, add your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>paste</strong> with your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
